message:
Combatting human trafficking is a collaborative effort. This is a great example of federal and local law enforcement agencies working across state lines to recover victims. 
"An investigation started July 5 after Columbus police received an email from the FBI regarding information from the Rogers Police Department in Arkansas, said police detective Mark Scruggs of the Special Victims Unit. It also indicated minors involved in sex trafficking." https://buff.ly/2N83bT6
